Template: percona-xtradb-cluster-server-5.7/really_downgrade
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Really proceed with downgrade?
 A file named /var/lib/mysql/debian-*.flag exists on this system.
 .
 Such file is an indication that a percona-xtradb-cluster-server package with a higher
 version has been installed earlier.
 .
 There is no guarantee that the version you're currently installing
 will be able to use the current databases.

Template: percona-xtradb-cluster-server-5.7/nis_warning
Type: note
Description: Important note for NIS/YP users
 To use MySQL, the following entries for users and groups should be added
 to the system:
 .
  /etc/passwd   : mysql:x:100:101:Percona XtraDB Cluster:/var/lib/mysql:/bin/false
  /etc/group    : mysql:x:101:
 .
 You should also check the permissions and the owner of the
 /var/lib/mysql directory:
 .
  /var/lib/mysql: drwxr-xr-x   mysql    mysql

Template: percona-xtradb-cluster-server-5.7/postrm_remove_databases
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Remove all Percona XtraDB Cluster databases?
 The /var/lib/mysql directory which contains the Percona XtraDB Cluster databases is
 about
 to be removed.
 .
 If you're removing the Percona XtraDB Cluster Server package in order to later install a more
 recent version or if a different percona-xtradb-cluster-server package is already
 using it, the data should be kept.

Template: percona-xtradb-cluster-server-5.7/start_on_boot
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Start the Percona XtraDB Cluster Server daemon on boot?
 The Percona XtraDB Cluster Server daemon can be launched automatically at boot time or
 manually with the '/etc/init.d/mysql start' command.

Template: percona-xtradb-cluster-server/root_password
Type: password
Description: New password for the Percona XtraDB Cluster "root" user:
 While not mandatory, it is highly recommended that you set a password
 for the Percona Server administrative "root" user.
 .
 If that field is left blank, the password will not be changed.

